ing this period.","summary":"Aavas Financiers aims for 25% disbursement growth by FY27.\nThe company is also expanding its branch network during this period.","url":"https://sqst.in/Yqdau","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-05T20:55:42","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"807203411993540992","title":"AAVAS Financiers' AUM rose 15% YoY to Rs. 222 bn; PAT up 13% YoY at Rs. 4.74 bn.\nSpread improved 40 bps to 5.34%, NIM at 7.82%; stable asset quality with 1+ DPD at 3.8%.","summary":"AAVAS Financiers' AUM rose 15% YoY to Rs. 222 bn; PAT up 13% YoY at Rs. 4.74 bn.\nSpread improved 40 bps to 5.34%, NIM at 7.82%; stable asset quality with 1+ DPD at 3.8%.","url":"https://sqst.in/L2VaG","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-05T16:28:10","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"473250","title":"Aavas Financiers' Q3 net profit rose to 1.7B INR from 1.46B INR YoY.\nRevenue increased to 5.74B INR in Q3, up from 5.12B INR YoY.","summary":"Aavas Financiers' Q3 net profit rose to 1.7B INR from 1.46B INR YoY.\nRevenue increased to 5.74B INR in Q3, up from 5.12B INR YoY.","url":"","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-05T16:26:50","source":"Livesquawk"},{"id":"807196260705222528","title":"AAVAS Financiers' board approved Q3 FY25 results: interest income INR 57,382 lakhs, PAT INR 17,005 lakhs.\nAFL Prime Lending Rate will be cut by 15 bps from March 1, 2026; NCDs have 100% security cover.","summary":"AAVAS Financiers' board approved Q3 FY25 results: interest income INR 57,382 lakhs, PAT INR 17,005 lakhs.\nAFL Prime Lending Rate will be cut by 15 bps from March 1, 2026; NCDs have 100% security cover.","url":"https://sqst.in/T4AbB","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-05T15:59:45","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"442346","title":"AAVAS Financiers confirmed timely interest payment on NCDs Series A & B.\nInterest payment totaled Rs. 16.88 crore on Jan 16, 2026, per SEBI norms.","summary":"AAVAS Financiers confirmed timely interest payment on NCDs Series A & B.\nInterest payment totaled Rs. 16.88 crore on Jan 16, 202